A 45-year-old man was arrested on the N9 between Uniondale and Harold yesterday, December 25, in Western Cape after police found mandrax tablets worth R3.75 million in his possession, George Herald reports. According to information, the Hawks followed up on information and spotted the white Hyundai minibus, and were assisted by the Outeniqua K9 dog unit from George and members from the Conville crime prevention unit. READ MORE: Alleged dealers nabbed with drugs worth R2.5m in KZN The bags of tablets were found hidden in a secret compartment in the roof of the minibus. The suspect is expected to appear in the George Magistrates&#8217; Court later this week. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.